   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>11</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  By <fr:link href="/schm-KSRJ/" title="Noetherian condition is affine local" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-KSRJ/" display-uri="schm-KSRJ" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-KSRJ/" display-uri="schm-KSRJ" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="/schm-4MZL/" title="Affine commutation" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-4MZL/" display-uri="schm-4MZL" type="local">affine commutation</fr:link>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is locally Noetherian, then any affine open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> is Noetherian. In particular, the intersection <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A \cap  \operatorname {Spec} B]]></fr:tex> for two affine open is <html:em>quasi-compact</html:em> by <fr:link href="/topl-00Q1/" title="Noetherian topological spaces have compact opens" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-00Q1/" display-uri="topl-00Q1" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-00Q1/" display-uri="topl-00Q1" /></fr:link>.
